declarations.comments: Delay all of a list's computations by one phase.
declarations.title: later

declarations.comments:
Insert a computation at the given index/"phase". The first phase is 0,
and providing a number lower than 0 also inserts at phase 0.
declarations.title: phase

declarations.comments: Fold a list of computations into a single computation.
declarations.title: foldPhases

declarations.comments:
Append a computation to the start of a list, applying the result of the
new computation to the result of the rest of the list.
declarations.title: cons

declarations.comments:
Append a computation to the start of a list, keeping only the result of
that first computation.
declarations.title: consFst

declarations.comments:
Append a computation to the start of a list, keeping only the result of
the tail of the list.
declarations.title: consSnd

declarations.comments:
Append a computation to the start of a list, providing a combining
function.
declarations.title: cons'

declarations.comments:
Get the computation at a certain index, returning `pure unit` if out of
bounds.
declarations.title: index

declarations.comments: Get the computation at a certain index.
declarations.title: index'

declarations.comments: Get the first computation, returning `pure unit` if there isn't one.
declarations.title: head

declarations.comments:
Get all the computations except the first, returning an empty list if there
are none.
declarations.title: tail

declarations.comments: Get all the computations except the first.
declarations.title: tail'

declarations.comments: Check if a list is empty.
declarations.title: null

declarations.comments: Find the length of a list.
declarations.title: length
